When I tell you it’s sooooo important to have a partner that REALLY listens to you. A few months into dating, I told Anthony that a goal of mine this year was to start reviewing hotels and guess what this man did…

One day he tells me that he booked a hotel in our hometown (Chicago) for me to do my first review (Eeeeekkk 🥹🤭🥰). Not only did he book the hotel but he also booked a videographer to capture everything so I wouldn’t have to do it myself. 

This man is so special and I love that he constantly shows up for me and invests in my dreams! I love you Black Man! 

Our first (3 part) hotel review drops Friday! I can’t wait to share this with you all ❤️

#hotelreview #blacklove #blackcouples #chicago

Hotel Review // Citizen M - Chicago (Part 1)

First let me start by saying, we were immediately enamored with the aesthetic and decor of this hotel! I love a good eclectic, funky, vibrant space — so this place was right up my alley.

The check in was also a green flag for us! I love anything self-served and hassle-free. But no worries, there’s always a staff member there to assist, if need be.

Additionally, as a remote worker, I can truly appreciate a hotel that has common space areas that can also serve as a co-working space. This hotel offers offices, desk with monitors and cute little private nooks for you to work and take calls. I’m obsessed! 

Special shoutout to The Hotel Manager Julian for taking some time out to sit and chat with us about all things @citizenm Chicago! 

Stay tuned for Part 2 🥂

Videographer: @focusprojectmedia 
#hotelreview #hotel #chicago #citizenm #travel #travelblogger

Hotel Review // Citizen M - Chicago (Part 2) 

It just gets better and better! We now take a look at more common areas and their lovely city view terrace! 

Side note: @nike @nikewomen we need a partnership the way we’re rocking these Pandas 🤭 (laughing but serious) 

Videographer: @focusprojectmedia 
#hotelreview #hoteldesign #hotel #citizenm #chicago

Hotel Review // Citizen M - Chicago (Part 3)

To be fully transparent, I almost made Anthony book another hotel because I was scared that we wouldn’t be able to fit in the bed, as we are both 6’2 and up! But I’m happy to announce that this room was TALL APPROVED! 

Everything in the room is controlled by the iPad —from the lighting and blinds to the TV— which was a very cool touch! We also loved how this perfectly sized room encouraged intimacy! (Side note for the couples: I do not recommend this hotel if you’re newly dating or shy about taking a 💩 in front of your partner lmao). 

And last, to my gym folk, this hotel has a fully equipped fitness center! We were truly impressed!

We hope you enjoyed this @citizenm - Chicago Hotel Review & Walkthrough! Let us know if you get a chance to check it out! 

Until next time! Cheers x

Videographer: @focusprojectmedia

I heard it’s #NationalLingerieDay 💕

My community on this platform has grown so much since I’ve stopped modeling full-time. But for those who are newer here, I started my modeling journey as a lingerie/swim model after winning @curvykate x @truemodelmgt model search in 2017! Winning this afforded me so many opportunities, including relocating to NYC and working in London! 

Being a lingerie model called for me to challenge the beauty standards that both me and the industry said I had to live up to. I was then able to build a platform encouraging women who looked like to me to love, embrace and flaunt the bawdyyyyyy they’re in! 

It still shocks me to this day to know that I was able to cross a major goal off my list in my early 20’s all while inspiring others. Wow! 

Happy National Lingerie Day! 

Love,
Tay xx

Prolactinoma is a noncancerous tumor of the pituitary gland. This tumor causes the pituitary gland to make too much of a hormone called prolactin. A prolactinoma isn’t life-threatening. But it can cause vision difficulties, infertility and other problems. Prolactinoma is the most common type of hormone-producing tumor that can develop in the pituitary gland.

Hello JUNE! 💐

The events that took place in May most definitely weren’t on my bingo card! I have never seen as many ambulance vehicles, ERs, hospitals, MRI machines and doctor offices in my life as much as I have in the past 31 days. 

But even still, I just want to say THANK YOU GOD! Thank you for your love and protection during this very scary, unexpected and uncertain time. You NEVER left my side! Thank you for the spirit of calmness you gave me while everything in my world felt turbulent. I felt your presence the entire time! Thank you for the unwavering love, prayers and support I received from my boyfriend, mother, family, friends and community. Thank you for my Doctors and Medical team at Cedar Sinai who provided the most amazing care for the week I was there, waiting for answers and a plan. I’ll forever have a praise of thanks on my lips because each day isn’t promised. So I’m grateful. 

Life has a interesting way of reminding you of what’s important. I’m crying as I type this because an unexpected health scare forced me to remember that life is truly truly precious. Do not to take it for granted because things can change in a heartbeat! Live, laugh, have fun and love on your people! 

June, I’m praying for continued healing and brighter days ❤️‍🩹 

Love,
Tay

🫂They Relieve Stress and Pain
Hugging often creates a feeling of calmness and relaxation due to Oxytocin — often called the “cuddle hormone.” This release can have a domino effect throughout the body and has been found to:
* Reduce inflammation
* Improve wound healing
* Lessen cravings for drugs, alcohol, and sweets
* Lower heart rate and stress 

🫂They Make Us Happier
Hugging increases Serotonin — a neurotransmitter known as the “feel good” hormone which helps us feel happy, calm, and confident.

🫂They Help Deepen Our Relationships
When you receive a hug from a partner, a friend or loved one, it can bring you comfort, make you feel safe, and sometimes even turn your entire day around. Hugs are a nonverbal understanding of each other and can deepen your connection with the person you’re sharing this moment with. It’s a form of meditation and they allow us to be present, to let go and flow with the energy of the embrace. Don’t underestimate the healing power of a hug!

I’ve been blessed with a partner who always shows up for me and has allowed me to ✨enter my soft girl era✨ However, I must admit, it’s been difficult to take the passenger seat sometimes and let him be the driver and lead. Maybe, it’s me being raised in a single parent household by an independent/boss lady OR maybe it’s the true headstrong Capricorn in me (lol). 

Whatever the reason, I’ve had to do some serious self-reflecting in this new relationship season to allow myself to be more soft, ask for help, & to let my partner be the MAN. Realizing that I no longer have to do it by myself (even if I can). 

Are there any other hyper-independent women that can relate?
